#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:2
msgid "Draw samples from a negative binomial distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:4
msgid ""
"Samples are drawn from a negative binomial distribution with specified "
"parameters, `n` successes and `p` probability of success where `n` is > 0 "
"and `p` is in the interval (0, 1]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:11
msgid "**n**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:-1
msgid "float or array_like of floats"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:11
msgid "Parameter of the distribution, > 0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:14
msgid "**p**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:14
msgid "Parameter of the distribution. Must satisfy 0 < p <= 1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:22
msgid "**size**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:-1
msgid "int or tuple of ints, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:17
msgid ""
"Output shape.  If the given shape is, e.g., ``(m, n, k)``, then ``m * n * "
"k`` samples are drawn.  If size is ``None`` (default), a single value is "
"returned if ``n`` and ``p`` are both scalars. Otherwise, ``np.broadcast(n, "
"p).size`` samples are drawn."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:0
msgid "Returns"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:36
msgid "**out**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:-1
msgid "ndarray or scalar"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:27
msgid ""
"Drawn samples from the parameterized negative binomial distribution, where "
"each sample is equal to N, the number of failures that occurred before a "
"total of n successes was reached."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:39
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:40
msgid "The probability mass function of the negative binomial distribution is"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:42
msgid ""
"P(N;n,p) = \\frac{\\Gamma(N+n)}{N!\\Gamma(n)}p^{n}(1-p)^{N},\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:44
msgid ""
"where :math:`n` is the number of successes, :math:`p` is the probability of "
"success, :math:`N+n` is the number of trials, and :math:`\\Gamma` is the "
"gamma function. When :math:`n` is an integer, :math:`\\frac{\\Gamma(N+n)}{N!"
"\\Gamma(n)} = \\binom{N+n-1}{N}`, which is the more common form of this term "
"in the pmf. The negative binomial distribution gives the probability of N "
"failures given n successes, with a success on the last trial."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:52
msgid ""
"If one throws a die repeatedly until the third time a \"1\" appears, then "
"the probability distribution of the number of non-\"1\"s that appear before "
"the third \"1\" is a negative binomial distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:56
msgid ""
"Because this method internally calls ``Generator.poisson`` with an "
"intermediate random value, a ValueError is raised when the choice of :math:"
"`n` and :math:`p` would result in the mean + 10 sigma of the sampled "
"intermediate distribution exceeding the max acceptable value of the "
"``Generator.poisson`` method. This happens when :math:`p` is too low (a lot "
"of failures happen for every success) and :math:`n` is too big ( a lot of "
"successes are allowed). Therefore, the :math:`n` and :math:`p` values must "
"satisfy the constraint:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:65
msgid ""
"n\\frac{1-p}{p}+10n\\sqrt{n}\\frac{1-p}{p}<2^{63}-1-10\\sqrt{2^{63}-1},\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.negative_binomial:67
msgid ""
"Where the left side of the equation is the derived mean + 10 sigma of a "
"sample from the gamma distribution internally used as the :math:`lam` "
"parameter of a poisson sample, and the right side of the equation is the "
"constraint for maximum value of :math:`lam` in ``Generator.poisson``."
msgstr ""

